The paper deals with remote sensing image classification using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the challenges of adapting DL methods to the specificities of remote sensing data, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed method involves optimizing computational costs, which could be relevant to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
